title: For Sale:  Heym/Westernfield Mauser 30-06
postcontent: This is a Westernfield Model 720B (30-06) commercial Mauser made by Heym of West Germany. Back in the day, before the Feds screwed things up, firearms manufacturers were commissioned by departments stores to make firearms for them under their brand name to sell to their customers (ie. Sears, JC Penney, Wards, etc.). Some of these were high quality rifles produced from world renowned companies such as FN of Belgium, Husqvarna of Sweden, Heym of Germany, and Voere of Austria just to name a few. This particular rifle is in very good condition and does not appear to have been used very much. These receivers stay more true to the original Mauser design in that they are of the "C" cut and not the "H" cut as seen by other companies in an attempt to ease manufacturing. To the best of my knowledge, the only thing not original to this rifle is the recoil pad. The stock does not appear to have been shortened, so if one chose to do so, they could replace it with an original pad. $460. Located in Enterprise.

title: For Sale:  High-End PISTON AR15
postcontent:
This is a meticulously crafted AR15 carbine length piston operated rifle.  This piece was built using extremely high quality components.

Operationally, it has a much higher cycling rate than a normal AR15, due to a light-weight Adams Arms bolt carrier group, and a buffer spring that retains mil-spec resistance.  The lower mass BCG is driven back faster than a heavy one is when the same force is applied (from the gas piston).  Similarly, the strong spring pushes a lighter weight group back faster than it would a heavy one.  

In order to take full advantage of this arrangement, you will need high quality magazines that can feed at that high cycling rate (Magpul PMAGs work extremely well) and a trigger that will allow you to perform successive shots rapidly.  This rifle has a Timney drop-in 3lb skeletonized competition trigger.  Highest quality trigger I've ever fired in my life.  Extremely fast and precise return.

Other components:
- BHW polygonal rifled stainless steel coated black 1:8 16" barrel with Saker muzzle brake/mount.  Produces higher muzzle velocity and accuracy due to less bullet deformation and sustains less wear than traditional rifling.
- Adams Arms gas block with settings for normal or suppressed fire.  Also has off mode single shot shooting.
- Fortis free-float handguard with dovetail barrel nut mount.  Fantastic mounting design.
- Magpul Stock with LaRue RISR cheek rest that slides back automatically when you pull the charging handle.
- Hogue Grip

Finally, Vortex Spitfire 3X Illuminated Optic.  Unbelievably clear glass, can illuminate in green and red.  Bright enough, even when looking directly at snow.  True combat optic as it will work without batteries as well, and then the reticle is simply black, like a traditional scope.  Excellent design.

I spent a ton of cash on this one and it's an outstanding rifle.  Has about 80 rounds through it, flawless.

Comes with 4 Magpul Gen3 Windowed 30Rd Magazines.
